    {
        "content": "<p>Ahh I left a comment there, but should have mentioned before posting. I realized this, but the theorem <code>takahashi_openRec</code> is not true without some side conditions. Consider:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">-- fvar \"y\"</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bvar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">abs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">fvar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"x\"</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">takahashi</span><span class=\"bp\">⟦</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↝</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fvar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"y\"</span><span class=\"bp\">⟧</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- bvar 1</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bvar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">abs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">fvar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"x\"</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"bp\">⟦</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↝</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fvar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"y\"</span><span class=\"bp\">⟧.</span><span class=\"n\">takahashi</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I couldn't figure out is being locally closed was sufficient, that's why it was commented out.</p>",
